The paper deals with facial age estimation using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of residual learning and decision forest also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the visualization of decision-making process, which could be relevant to computer graphics (cs.CR) sub-category.
